Alright. I surrender. All the comments and sarcasm make it clear to me
that my points and attempts here are lost. I&#39;m not new to the field
and I know the importance of having some protocol but... not everyone
feels the same. That&#39;s okay. Unless your like Frank R and are only in
this for yourself, then your truly not a serious researcher in the
true definition of the word. 
I do appreciate everyone&#39;s time though. I won&#39;t bother anyone here
again. My email address is babiarz3@... for those who wish to
continue the discussion. Take care everyone.

Babs


--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Lisby &lt;lisby@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; If I misunderstood, then I certainly apologize.
&gt; 
&gt; Perhaps we&#39;d react differently if you participated here more often-- 
&gt; posting your own files and asking questions of researchers. For  
&gt; example, &quot;Hey, Ann--that file you just posted, I hear what you do,  
&gt; but is anything clipped out of it? I think I hear a track silenced,  
&gt; too. If so, why did you do that?&quot; Then I get to answer and explain  
&gt; why I did it that way, offer the raw clip, or whatever. It doesn&#39;t  
&gt; come off as a broad attack--just a friendly question. Even Bruce  
&gt; wouldn&#39;t rip out your living eyeballs for that. (Well... maybe he  
&gt; wouldn&#39;t, anyway. ;) )
&gt; 
&gt; I agree with your search for The Truth. I really do. That&#39;s why you  
&gt; see me get all rough-and-tumble over stuff like the Luminator when I  
&gt; think it is it lacking convincing evidence. But it&#39;s waaaaaay too  
&gt; early in &quot;boxology&quot; to try to make it perform as a pet circus animal.  
&gt; Hell, we&#39;ve been studying traditional EVP for 30 years and it still  
&gt; won&#39;t perform on cue for the scientists or anyone else. But if you  
&gt; just listen to what you get on your own and what all the others are  
&gt; getting, it becomes very clear indeed that a real phenomenon is  
&gt; occurring. Sure, some things we get that we think are paranormal may  
&gt; be just radio fragments, but one radio fragment does not negate all  
&gt; box communication. One tweaked clip is not indicative of a culture of  
&gt; researcher deceit. One &quot;I am Bazoozoo! Time to fry, foolish mortal!&quot;  
&gt; does not mean that the RS hacks are pathways to Satan&#39;s indoor  
&gt; plumbing. There are no easy answers yet--and there may never be any.  
&gt; And I&#39;m not sure we&#39;re at the stage yet where we have the right to  
&gt; demand The Truth or whether we would even see it if it was staring us  
&gt; in the face.
&gt; 
&gt; All right, enough joy in myself one-hand clapping.
&gt; 
&gt; LC is right that if you want to try to pursue this in the way you  
&gt; want to pursue it, then you need to find some people who share your  
&gt; mindset and go to it. I don&#39;t think you&#39;re going to find those people  
&gt; here, necessarily--at least among the old guard. We&#39;re the beatniks  
&gt; in black leather, smoking ciggies and reading bad poetry to the beat  
&gt; of bongos, HMO.
&gt; 
&gt; Ann
&gt; 
&gt; On Jan 21, 2008, at 1:37 PM, babiarz3 wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; &gt; Just to clear things up.. the file I&#39;m referring to is not from anyone
&gt; &gt; involved in this group so when I say that occasionally I hear their
&gt; &gt; voices become shaky, that is not a comment on anyone here. Also,
&gt; &gt; please don&#39;t misread what I actually said. The point I made, or tried
&gt; &gt; to make, about the investigators not hearing what I heard... I
&gt; &gt; wouldn&#39;t have heard all of it in real time either. Too many layers,
&gt; &gt; too fast, etc. I have the luxury now of sitting and analyzing the file
&gt; &gt; in my own time.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; As for fear being a factor... I do believe that the attitude of the
&gt; &gt; investigators present during a session does effect the outcome. Even
&gt; &gt; Bruce who would rather cut my eyeballs out with a razor has said the
&gt; &gt; same. If you think that I am scared, fine. If I&#39;m missing one thing it
&gt; &gt; is probably a healthy dose of fear. Don&#39;t make the mistake of missing
&gt; &gt; the points by name calling.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; I post my thoughts here because it is an active group of people
&gt; &gt; working with this form of ITC. You can call me a shit stirrer or
&gt; &gt; whatever you want. The point is that I see issues that could be
&gt; &gt; addressed fairly easily. You can ignore it or deflect all you want.
&gt; &gt; For me, it&#39;s not about being friends, it&#39;s about the research.
